 Creapiing was restless, the duties of her office bearing down upon her shoulders as never before.  On days like this there was nothing to do but go fishing.  She rose, turned from her desk, and went to grab her pole and the carefully tied flies that she had made and placed here.  One of the sharp hooks punctured her finger and she smiled as she licked the blood.  <br>
<br>
A random thought that she still owed Khasirath a dinner and an evening of debate crossed her mind, and she turned to her desk to write the note inviting him.   She smiled thinking he would surely bring the pickled lizard that creapiing so loved.<br>
<br>
Creapiiing stoppped.  Spreading across her desk like so much fresh blood, the red ink soaked into the parchements there, dripped onto her chair and the beautifully woven carpets.  Visions of blood, flashes of those she had killed, blood she had drunk, ceremonies she had performed.  Blood --the essence of her life.<br>
<br>
Let me tell you a story a low voice whispered from behind her.  Creapiing stood completely still.  She froze knowing that somehow they had finally found a way to bribe their way in.  Today would be the day then.  She felt confident, strong.<br>
<br>
You see, Creapiing, your grandfather, whose armor you wear, my father, he is not as you perceived.  You have forsaken your family, your destiny, to pursue a life of honor.  Honor , the word rasped scathingly from her Mothers lips.   Creapiing tensed.  No, her mother continued, let me finish my story.  The voice continued, smoothly and from behind her, Creapiing did not move, knowing that to move now was death, she waited her opportunity.  Your Grandfather was not the honorable shadowknight you have fashioned yourself after.  He was a rogue, like me, the voice hissed.  He was the greatest deceiver in our family, a real legend.  He infiltrated the ranks of the best families in his guise.  He theived, manipulated, and yes, even assassinated.  He is yet honored as the one of the greatest shadowknights, but that prestige pales next to the legends of him and his deeds in the ranks of the Unseen Hands.<br>
<br>
The triumph in her mothers voice was clear as she continued, and now , my daughter, you have placed yourself in a position to become greater then your Grandfather.  You have infiltrated the Violent Harvest.  You have been very clever, daughter.  You have reputation, indisputed honor, and you are free to move about the city as you wish.  What fortune, what destiny is now in your hands to grasp.  Remember your training.<br>
<br>
The rage inside Creapiing built to an inferno pounding in her ears.  All reason left as she grabbed at painbringer and brought the weapon around to kill  her mother.   She saw nothing, but breathed in particles of dust that felt like a million needles in her throat and lungs.  Gasping, she clawed at her face and screamed in agony, or it seemed like she screamed --but no sound emerged.  Her mother emerged from the corner, hidden right in front of her eyes, Creapiing moaned.<br>
<br>
The agony was intense, and Creapiings Mother bent slowly over and kissed her on the forehead.  We claim you again as one of us, she whispered.  The threatening blackness cascaded upon her.<br>
<br>
