<br>
Flashes of the euphoria she had once had in this very pool went through her mind.  Khasirath pulling her body from the pool, both nearly drowned.  The longing she felt to cool her fevered body in its depths.<br>
<br>
Not this time.  She pushed her body harder and deeper into the embrace of the deep dark water.  Creapiings lungs ached.  The euphoria was a threatening cloud on her mind.  The darkness was overwhelming in this shadow of Neriak.  The depths blacker then an ebony drake.<br>
<br>
Creapiings hand scraped on rock.  Frenzied, she felt around.  The last of her air was gone.  Her hands moved frantically with the adrenaline of knowing she would drown soon.  Like  a manta she skimmed the bottom and sought three stones stacked in a pyramid.  What was she trying to remember?  Thoughts came sporadically.  Yes, an Air tube.  An escape route used by her rogue parents.  She tugged at the top boulder and pulled out a slim tube.  The top was cleverly capped so that it remained full of air.  She took a deep breath then gagged at the stale air.  Wet molds had grown in the long disuse of this tube.<br>
<br>
The air was foul, but it was enough.  Calm.  She forced calm upon herself.  Creapiing took another breath, trying to force the molds to the side of her mouth, and keep them out of her lungs.  Such a clever device.  Undoubtedly stolen from the gnomes.  Or tortured from them...<br>
<br>
Looking aroung Creapiing saw the opening she sought.  A small tunnel that would take her to the little known passageways.  Swimming smoothly now, her path assured, Creapiing turned toward the tunnel.<br>
<br>
