<br>
Like the winged shadows she slid down the passage towards Freeport.  A smile lit her face at the pleasure she was going to take from this.  She emerged just inside Freeport into a city dotted with fires to hide the blessed darkness of Innoruuk.  She merged with the side of a house.  She waited.<br>
<br>
Please, I just lost all my gear, do you have anything I can have?  The words whined pitifully out the dwarf.  Creapiing smiled.  His boots from beneath his cloak gave him away.  A begger.  A dwarf begger.  Creapiing felt a surge of anticipation.  The citizen moved on after giving the rich begger some coin.  Creapiing stalked him into an alley.  The dwarf was counting his coin.  <br>
<br>
Silent death.  Thud.   Creapiing took the coin.  She tugged off his cloak.  She grabbed his flask.  Dwarven ale..foul but sufficient.  A dagger, she smiled.  The rest she would leave, for the freeport carrion to pick clean.  These humans were much worse then the rats.  Silent as Death she went  into the tunnels toward Neriak once again.  She still had one loose end to attend.<br>
