<br>
Stealthily she approached Neriak from a different angle then before.  The Reaper of the Harvest was gone.  This woman with scratched face and short hair did not even resemble her former self.  One last thing to do, one last end to tie to assure her success.<br>
<br>
Hiding deep within the cloak Creapiing had taken from the Dwarven begger, she walked quickly and silently through the streets.  The city was humming with activity and it was long after the sun was up.  Creapiing smiled.  They were undoubtedly dredging the waterways looking for her body even now.  <br>
<br>
For a long time, Creapiing had slept in a different house, inn, or even corner each evening.  By avoiding the same location twice she minimized the likelihood of being poisoned or attacked.  She approached the inn where she had been expected to sleep at this eve.  Only one other person knew the location.  That person would be there waiting, with warm food at the ready and freshly laid blankets for her.<br>
<br>
Steadily, stealthily, she went up the stairs to her room.  Soundlessly she opened up the door to her room.  The food was ready, the blankets laid.  Kurmudgins back was to her.  He awaited her in the ill fitting clothes and armor that she kept him dressed in.  He was entirely non descript except for his enormous form.<br>
<br>
Soundlessly she walked across the room.  Quickly and accurately she drove the dagger she had stolen off the dwarf beggers body into the back of Kurmudgins neck.  With amazing quickness and strength the troll turned on her.  She moved with him as best as she could pushing downward with all her strength on the dagger.  The trolls massive arms came around and beat upon her.  Creapiing gasped for breath as the stumps pounded on her and she pressed harder and harder upon the blade.<br>
<br>
With a snap the blade broke.  The sudden release made Creapiing lose her balance and she rushed forward and tripped and fell on her face.  Blackness descended on her.  When  Creapiing awoke the was aching everywhere and an enormous weight had her pinned to the floor.  With a rush it all came back.  The stickiness on her face was blood.  Summoning what little strength she had left, Creapiing rolled the enormous body off of her.  Kurmudgins slow brain had not allowed him to admit he was dead until his attacker lay at his feet.  Then he had fallen upon her.  Gingerly she checked her ribs.  She seemed to have come out mostly unharmed.<br>
<br>
The tea and food was still tepid and Creapiings stomach rumbled.  She forced herself to sit and eat and drink.  Then quietly, she stripped off the too small armor and weapons from the troll.  No one questioned the quality of the armor she had given her slave.  The ill fit had turned aside curiousity.  These supple leathers would fit her much more now then the plate mail she had worn yesterday.  The stillettos fit her hand nicely.  <br>
<br>
Not one person would ever mistake Creapiing for less then extremely dangerous.  And not one would recognize her as the *former* Reaper of the Violent Harvest.   Dressed she noisely left the room and walked out of the inn to listen to the rumors on the streets, and to send a message.<br>
