<br>
Creapiing sprawled out on a comfortable bed snoring loudly.  Her bath had been cleansing.  The removal of the grime made all the pain and fatigue of the last day rush to meet her, and she had happily laid down to reset herself for the work yet to come.<br>
<br>
Choking she awoke to the Mad Ones laughter, and spat the rancid wine back at him.  Mad One, she warned, never approach me in my sleep again, or ...die..., She whispered the last word more as a truth then a threat.  Are the rest assembling?  She cautiously took the flask and then took a long drink.  Like the heat of Lavastorm, the liquor rushed through her veins.  She reached to straighten her hair our of  habit, but found none to straighten. <br>
<br>
Dark names, dark shadows. assembled under the cabin in the wood.  Nospiratus....Creapiing....Vinar...Imrahil... Xosha...Ixtab...Ueudiinya... Names of power.  Innoruuk himself must have felt the tremor in Norrath and he graced this meeting with a dark presence.  Parchment seemed thrown about the room and those inside  argued and debated through the night.<br>
