<br>
Vinars arm moved above them all briefly and a red glow swaddled the group and then they disappeared leaving only a red mist swirling.<br>
<br>
Creapiing felt the rush of remembering.  Her feet instictively moved silently.  All the years of rogue training congealed in her, tempered by her time as a Shadowknight of Innoruuk.   Her time was now.  All these years she had hated.  She had hated rogues.  She had hated her parents.  She had hated herself.  Today, her hate solidified into a single mass of strength, confidence. and purpose.  Today, she was not revered leader of the Violent Harvest, but rather a single pair of legs of the centipede that would forever change the face of Norrath.<br>
<br>
The group stood there, confident that no one saw them, but each looking to see if anyone noticed them.  Stilletos and main gauches flickered in every hand.  They walked silently and swiftly toward their objective.<br>
<br>
Mistmoor was filled with undead, huge gargoyles that loomed and popped to life if anyone strayed too close, and warped shrieking creatures to horrible for description.  Apprentices and students walked through this evil place.  The group moved silently and unnoticed.  They approached the castle mistmoor from the graveyard, filtering in through the invisible walls and hidden doorways.  Past the guards, they slid undetected.<br>
<br>
The opulence of this place was truly astounding.  Plush carpets and artistry were everywhere.   Creapiing doubted anyone had ever gotten so deep within Mistmoors walls before undetected.  Mythral had done well in disarming all the sigils.  The lure of his inheritence and disdain for his family had made Mythral a willing accomplice.<br>
<br>
Mayong Mistmoor was planning his next move.  He poured over maps in the Castle Mistmoor today.  Your time has come, a voice whispered in his ear.  Then his blood splurted from eight separate wounds and soaked the carpets and parchements around him.  Creapiing reached down, unhooked the axe from mayong, and with  a chop, finished their business in the Castle Mistmoor.<br>
<br>
In a swirl of red, they disappeared.<br>
<br>
-----<br>
<br>
A bag landed with a solid thud upon the desk of Daiunus, newly appointed Thresher of the Violent Harvest.  His assistant shrugged unknowingly.  Just arrived, he said, it came with this envelope.  <br>
<br>
Daiunus reached first for the envelope.  Thresher.  The one word upon it.  Gingerly he opened the envelop and pulled out a thick parchement and began to read:<br>
<br>
<br>
    Daiunus, newly appointed Thresher for the Violent Harvest, let us introduce ourselves.  Under the leadership of the Subati Razorback, a special ministry was formed called the Breagan D'Aerthe.  The Breagan D'Aerthe is a single unit that exists for clandestine operations both on their own initiative and at the request of the Thresher of the Violent Harvest.  We report to no one else.   Though most consider our existence to be rumor or myth, we would like to assure you that we do indeed exist.<br>
<br>
  At this time we choose to remain anonymous, though some or all of us may choose to reveal ourselves to you in the future should you prove to be strong in hate and Innoruuks blessings.<br>
<br>
  As a token, we have sent you a gift that represents our latest intervention in the operations of Norrath.<br>
<br>
  Should you ever need us you may leave a message with the hafling that swims inside the glass at the blind fish.<br>
<br>
The Breagan D'Aerthe<br>
